BFN 

  [Excerpt] The Rwandan Patriotic Army [RPA] continues to 
score points. The international airport at Kanombe near Kigali 
and the Kanombe camp of Colonel (Mayuya) are under the total 
control of the RPA, the armed wing of the Rwandan Patriotic 
Front [RPF], as of this morning. Under siege for several days, 
the Col. (Mayuya) camp finally fell today to the combatants of 
the RPA. Many soldiers left their [word indistinct] behind. 
Enormous quantities of arms were seized. Government troops who 
fled the onslaught of the Inkotanyi [rebels] did not have time 
to take their arms and ammunition. [passage omitted] 

